<br>
Republicans collect money from businesses, and in general, try to pass legislation to allow businesses to flourish (sometimes to a fault).<br>
<br>
Democrats collect money from labor unions and trial lawyers and therefore like to pass laws that allow for unlimited liability, tougher hiring/firing rules, bigger government, etc.<br>
<br>
Neither party is really 'great' anymore. Both are mostly whorish. Republicans have taken an upper hand as of late, as they have fewer special interests to try and appease.<br>
<br>
As for history, it was abraham lincoln's republican party that freed the slaves back in the 1800's. So the perspective on where each party stands depends on what part of the country you live in. Since the Emancipation Proclaimation 140 or so years ago, republicans have not done all that well in the south. This has led to some shifting, and democrats elected from southern states tend to be very conservative in their politics...... <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929"> Naladini </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
